00:18.118 --> 00:19.887 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The U.S. Supreme
Court has
set the stage for a major
election-year decision

00:19.920 --> 00:21.722 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on immigration policy. The
justices announced
today they will consider whether
President

00:21.755 --> 00:22.956 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Obama overstepped his authority
when he allowed
millions of people to avoid
deportation. We

00:22.990 --> 00:24.958 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
will explore this in full right
after the
news summary.

00:24.992 --> 00:26.760 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
There's word that three
Americans who disappeared
in Baghdad last week were
kidnapped by a Shiite

00:26.793 --> 00:32.032 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
militia. Reuters reported that
today, citing
Iraqi and U.S. sources. It said
the group

00:32.065 --> 00:37.371 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is backed by Iran, but that U.S.
officials
don't think Iran's government
was involved

00:37.404 --> 00:39.406 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in the abduction.

00:39.439 --> 00:43.977 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Iraqi civilians are being killed
at a -- quote
-- "staggering rate" since the
rise of the

00:44.011 --> 00:52.185 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Islamic State group. A U.N.
report now says
that at least 18,800 Iraqis died
from violence

00:52.219 --> 00:55.322 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
