the lowest rate
since 1990, 6.9 percent. In
turn, the International

01:42.803 --> 01:48.842 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Monetary Fund announced in
London that it's
revising its global forecast
down again.

01:48.875 --> 01:53.013 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAURICE OBSTFELD, International
Monetary Fund:
Turbulence in financial markets
has returned

01:53.046 --> 01:58.285 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
amid renewed concern about risks
to global
economic growth. China's slower
growth and

01:58.318 --> 02:04.424 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
rising financial market risks,
the fall in
commodity prices, notably the
price of oil,

02:04.458 --> 02:11.999 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and asynchronous trends in
monetary policy
mainly between the U.S. and most
other advanced

02:12.032 --> 02:13.800 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
economies.

02:13.834 --> 02:17.337 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We will take a
closer look
at the Chinese economy later in
the program.

02:17.371 --> 02:23.944 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
