said today
that it expects this year's
deficit will top

02:28.081 --> 02:35.489 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
$540 billion, $100 billion more
than last
year. The main cause is
Congress' recent decision

02:35.522 --> 02:41.094 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to make a number of tax cuts
permanent and
to increase spending. At the
same time, the

02:41.128 --> 02:47.501 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
economy will grow 2.7 percent,
down from an
earlier estimate.

02:47.534 --> 02:52.672 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the presidential race,
Republican Donald
Trump has won the backing of
former Alaska

02:52.706 --> 02:59.012 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
