23:41.453 --> 23:47.693 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We have agreed to have a
process, a channel,
a consular channel to continue
discussions,

23:47.726 --> 23:52.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
should that be necessary. The
case of Robert
Levinson, of course, was the
topic of conversation

23:52.731 --> 23:57.603 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
every single round. As we said
in 2011, we
have to reason to believe he's
not being held

23:57.636 --> 23:59.672 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in Iran, so it's a different
case.

23:59.705 --> 24:08.113 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: There is another
American -- Iranian-American
still being held, Mr. Namazi.
How cruel is

24:08.147 --> 24:11.517 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it to leave them behind and let
these others
-- other five out?

24:11.550 --> 24:15.554 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRETT MCGURK: Any other cases, I
can't really
discuss in detail, for privacy
reasons and

24:15.587 --> 24:20.125 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
things, but I would just say
we're going to
continue to work, work this
every day.

24:20.159 --> 24:23.962 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In terms of what
happened,
there are critics in this
country who are

24:23.996 --> 24:28.967 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
saying this swap should never
have happened,
that these people were -- should
never have

24:29.001 --> 24:33.339 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
been held in the first place and
the U.S.
shouldn't have done anything in
return to

24:33.372 --> 24:35.207 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
win their release.

24:35.240 --> 24:40.979 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRETT MCGURK: I think the
reality is, if you
take that position, then Jason
Rezaian should

24:41.013 --> 24:44.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have stayed in Evin prison for
decades. Amir
Hekmati would have been in
prison through

24:44.850 --> 24:48.954 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
2022, and Saeed Abedini until
about the same
time.

24:48.987 --> 24:53.859 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So that was the reality that you
face. There
was no way to simply say, they
have to be

24:53.892 --> 24:56.995 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
