can't get them
out by just saying, hey, get
them out. And

25:09.074 --> 25:16.615 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
so we had to figure out a
formula. And I think
if you really look at it, in
terms of, on

25:16.648 --> 25:25.057 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Iranian side, you're looking
at nonviolent
individuals, all -- some of them
quite elderly,

25:25.090 --> 25:30.696 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
people who in some cases their
sentences were
about the run in less than a
year anyway.

25:30.729 --> 25:34.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Most of them would have been out
of prison
before even the first of the
Americans were

25:34.666 --> 25:41.874 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to be out of prison. Given the
category of
cases we're talking about, of
sanctions violations,

25:41.907 --> 25:46.011 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
three of them had been
convicted, three of
them were pending trial, and one
was about

25:46.044 --> 25:50.783 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to plead his case. So, only
three were actually
in prison.

25:50.816 --> 25:54.186 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think if you look at that and
you consider
what the stakes were if we could
not find

25:54.219 --> 25:59.558 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a way forward here for these
Americans in
Evin prison, at the end of the
day, I think

25:59.591 --> 26:01.326 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the president made the right
call here.

26:01.360 --> 26:06.231 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: You said that
there is no way
to know whether this deal, these
deals will

26:06.265 --> 26:11.170 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
lead to something productive in
the future
between the U.S. and Iran. But,
specifically,

26:11.203 --> 26:16.074 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
do you see something, some
movement on their
part when it comes to Syria?

26:16.108 --> 26:18.777 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRETT MCGURK: We have this
Vienna process
in which the Iranians are at the
table and

26:18.811 --> 26:23.715 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Saudis are at the table for
the first
time since the Iranian -- Syrian
civil war

26:23.749 --> 26:25.751 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
broke out about five years ago.

26:25.784 --> 26:29.788 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's encouraging, but
that's a very
difficult process. I think,
look, Iran is

26:29.822 --> 26:33.725 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a country that's going --
undergoing some
fundamental questions about its
future. It

26:33.759 --> 26:38.597 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
