28:58.270 --> 29:04.142 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And they're having a rocky time
doing that.
That is in progress, but it's a
tough balancing

29:04.176 --> 29:06.979 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
act, and I think it's not going
quite as smoothly
as they had hoped.

29:07.012 --> 29:09.581 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right, we
will get to the
larger model change.

29:09.615 --> 29:13.051 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, Eswar Prasad, first, this
big question:
How much of a slowdown? What do
you see?

29:13.085 --> 29:15.687 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ESWAR PRASAD, Professor of Trade
Policy, Cornell
University: China's economy has
been powered

29:15.721 --> 29:19.725 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
by the manufacturing sector.
